This code defines a WebSocket connection to the server using the `io()` method, and listens for the `response` event using the `socket.on('response', ...)` method. When a new `response` event is received, we update the UI with the resulting response.

On the user input side, we listen for the click event of the send button and send a `user_input` event to the server using `socket.emit('user_input', ...)`. The user input prompt is also appended to the UI.

